Acsa says its fueling depot at Cape Town International Airport experienced technical problems during routine maintenance. CAPE TOWN - Flights out of Cape Town are experiencing delays due to temporary refueling challenges.Airports Company South Africa (Acsa) says its fueling depot at Cape Town International Airport experienced technical problems during routine maintenance earlier on Thursday.This required a full shutdown of the fueling system.Acsa s Deidre Davids said: Restarting the system has various safety protocolsand that does take a little bit of time. It has had an impact on departing flights and all operational staff have been deployed to try and keep passengers informed. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)